# ECZ EoC Syllabus Spec (every subject)

Every ECZ subject assessment scheme must live as one JSON file under `data/curriculum/ecz-eoc/`, conforming to `EczSubjectSpec` in `lib/ecz/eoc/ecz-eoc-spec.schema.ts`.

## Canonical examples

- **Mathematics I (topic-mode):** `data/curriculum/ecz-eoc/mathematics-i-2021.json`
- **Agricultural Science (topic + taskType):** `data/curriculum/ecz-eoc/agricultural-science-4018.json`
- **Physics / Chemistry / Biology / Geography:** `physics-4016.json`, `chemistry-4014.json`, `biology-4012.json`, `geography-3014.json`
- **Source of truth for extracts:** `Validation_folder/ECSEOL Assessment Schemes_22_4_2026.pdf` (+ chapter text under `Validation_folder/extracted_chapters/`)

## Required top-level shape

```json
{
  "subjectCode": "4018",
  "subjectName": "Agricultural Science",
  "syllabusYear": 2024,
  "construct": "…",
  "elementsOfConstruct": [ /* EoC1…EoCn */ ],
  "testDesign": { "components": [], "scenarioRequired": true, "minPartsPerScenarioItem": 2 },
  "scoringCriteria": { "rules": [] },
  "exemplars": []
}
```

## EoC rules

- Each EoC has `id` (`EoC1`…), `description`, `subSkills[]`, and `resolutionMode` (`topic` | `taskType`).
- Sub-skills carry `topicAliases` (verified CDC wording), `unverifiedTopicAliases` (provisional), optional `taskTypeAliases` + `note`.
- `resolutionMode: "topic"` → match syllabus topic names (Maths style).
- `resolutionMode: "taskType"` → skill-lens EoCs (investigation / analysis / project); topics only as unverified anchors.
- Do **not** invent EoCs, marks, or Bloom ranges not present in the Assessment Schemes PDF.
- Register new subjects in `SPEC_FILES` inside `lib/ecz/eoc/load-eoc-spec.ts`.
- Validate generated items with `validateQuestion` / `validateStructure` from `lib/ecz/eoc/question-validator.ts` — never skip for AI quiz / ECZ practice.

## Filename convention

`{subject-slug}-{subjectCode|year}.json` e.g. `agricultural-science-4018.json`, `mathematics-i-2021.json`.
